				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I would like to see some kind of an implementation of <strong>meta-effects</strong>, effects that one could program to "command" other effects and thus create complex sounds with more ease. For example, the user could pre-define a certain single effect letter to abbreviate for a long and thoroughly complex guitar-like-pitch-bending, volume-changing and arpeggio-abusing effect pattern with only a single effect.
<br />
<br />Of course, getting such a feature to run 240 times a second on an old 6502 is most likely not that easy. Perhaps possible for a single, maybe even two, channels, but, I dare say, certainly not possible for every single one.
<br />Then again, as an experienced musician, you most likely already have a brilliant strategy to combat the adversity of having to write down long, repeating sequences.
<br />
<br />To address the matter of limited space, have you considered bankswitched SRAM?</div>

